api_list.name: createAccessKey
api_list.description: Create a new API Key for the project.

required_parameters.name: isActive
required_parameters.description: A boolean that indicates if the key is currently active or revoked.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: A human readable name for the API Key. Limited to 256 characters.

required_parameters.name: options
required_parameters.description: An object containing more details about the key’s permitted and restricted functionality.

required_parameters.name: permitted
required_parameters.description: A list of high level actions this key can perform. Possible options: “writes”, “queries”, “saved_queries”, “cached_queries”, “datasets”, “schema”

api_list.name: createCachedDataset
api_list.description: Create a Cached Dataset.

required_parameters.name: displayName
required_parameters.description: The human-readable string name for your Cached Dataset

required_parameters.name: query
required_parameters.description: The query definition you want Keen to optimize for your application.

required_parameters.name: indexBy
required_parameters.description: The event property name of string values you will to retrieve results by; eg “product.id” stored as “1f2o3o4”, “5b6a7r8”. Currently supports one index_by property name. Cannot duplicate property query’s group_by.

api_list.name: createCachedQuery
api_list.description: By turning on caching, you can tell Keen to automatically refresh your saved queries so you can get immediate results. We will calculate the results of your query on a set interval, and have them available for you immediately when you ask for the Saved Query result.

required_parameters.name: refreshRate
required_parameters.description: The refresh rate value is in seconds, and must be more than 1 hour (3,600 seconds) and less than 24 hours (86,400 seconds).

required_parameters.name: queryName
required_parameters.description: Change the name of the query.

api_list.name: createEvent
api_list.description: Records a single event to a given event collection.

api_list.name: createExtractionRequest
api_list.description: Creates an extraction request for full-form event data with all property values.

required_parameters.name: eventCollection
required_parameters.description: Specifies the name of the event collection to analyze.

required_parameters.name: timeframe
required_parameters.description: Refines the scope of events to be included in the analysis based on when the event occurred.

optional_parameters.name: email
optional_parameters.description: If an email address is specified, an email will be sent to it when your extraction is ready for download. If email is not specified, your extraction will be processed synchronously and your data will be returned as JSON.

optional_parameters.name: filters
optional_parameters.description: Refines the scope of events to be included in the analysis based on event property values.

optional_parameters.name: latest
optional_parameters.description: An integer containing the number of most recent events to extract.

optional_parameters.name: timezone
optional_parameters.description: Assigns a timezone offset to relative timeframes.

api_list.name: createMultipleEvents
api_list.description: Record multiple events across one or more event collections.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: Specifies the name of the project to be created.

required_parameters.name: users
required_parameters.description: Specifies users for the project. If any users supplied do not exist, the request will fail. You will receive an error indicating which users are invalid.

api_list.name: getProjectDatasets
api_list.description: Get list of Cached Dataset definitions for a project

optional_parameters.name: limit
optional_parameters.description: How many Cached Dataset definitions to return at a time (1-100). Defaults to 10.

optional_parameters.name: afterName
optional_parameters.description: A cursor for use in pagination. after_name is the Cached Dataset name that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 Cached Dataset definitions, ending with dataset_foo you can use dataset_foo as your after_name to retrieve the next page of definitions. Lists also return with helper “next_page_url” that uses after_name, so your subsequent call can fetch the next page of the list easily.
